The patient was a 36-year-old Niger national who worked for a transport company, the government said on Thursday. He had travelled to Lome, Accra, Abidjan and Ouagadougou. The patient was stable and efforts were ongoing to contain the virus, the government added. Niger becomes the latest country in Africa to confirm it has coronavirus. Religious leaders in the country have issued a joint statement suspending worship at mosques and churches to prevent the spread of the virus. President, Issoufou Mahamadou urged people to keep calm and to respect preventative measure. "God willing, together we will overcome this ordeal," he tweeted. --BBC--